
Terraform is a Infrastructure as a code 

Infrastructure as a code means managing and creating infrastructure using code instead of manual UI creation

Advantages of Terraform

MultiCloud Support
state managemenet
execution plan

Terraform architecture

init  
validate
fmt
plan
apply
destroy


Terraform workflow 

write--->Init--->plan--->apply--->destroy

developer writes .tf files
       |
       |
terraform init
       |
       |
providers downloaded
       |
       |
terraform plan
       |
       |
authentication with cloud
       |
       |
terraform apply
       |
       |
state updated


.tf --- configuration files
.tfstate --- infrastructure truth
.terraform --- plugins 


StateFile:-  terraform.tfstate

desiredstate==actualstate

remote backend storage -S3,blob

Imp points 

store statefile into remote backend
do not update/delete the file
state locking
isolation of statefile
regular backup

State locking :-prevent multiple people from running terraform at the same time on the same infrastructure
if process crashes manually remove lock 
terraform force-unlock <LOCK_ID>


